e is hopelessly busted, since} 28.Rxg7 {is met by} Be4+ 29. R1g2 Bxg2+ 30. Rxg2 Rxe3 {, winning.}) ({c)} 26. Bh6$2 {fails to} Bxh6 $1 27. Qxh6 ({after} 27. Rxg8+ $4 Rxg8 {, Black threatensmates on e4 and also f2, to which there is no good defence}) 27... Qf8 28. Qh5Qf5 29. Qh6 Nf2+ 30. Kg1 Ng4 31. Qd2 Rg8 {. Black defended successfully andshould convert.}) 26... d4 $1 {Attacking White's bishop, who watches over thef2 fork square.} 27. cxd4 cxd4 28. Rd1 {White's only move.} dxe3 29. Rxd3 Rc8 {Black uses the lull to threaten White's back rank.} 30. Rdxe3 Bd4 $1 31. Re1 {White must cover his first rank.} ({Not} 31. Reg3 $4 {, when Black forces matewith} Rc1+ 32. Kg2 Rg1+ 33. Kf3 Qf8+ 34. Kg4 Qc8+ 35. Kf4 Qc7+ 36. Kg4 Qd7+ 37.Kh4 ({or} 37. Kf3 Qc6+ 38. Kf4 Qe4+ 39. Kg5 Qf5+ 40. Kh4 Bf6+ 41. Qg5 Bxg5+ 42.Rxg5 Qxg5#) 37... Bf6+ {and game over.}) 31... Bxb2 $6 {Black doesn't havetime for this pawn grab.} ({He has good chances to consolidate after} 31... Rf8$1 32. b3 Qg7 {.}) 32. Rg1 $6 ({White misses a chance to split the point:} 32.Qb5 $1 Bc3 33. Re7 Bg7 34. Rxh7+ $1 Qxh7 35. Re8+ Rxe8 36. Qxe8+ Qg8 37. Qh5+Qh7 38. Qe8+ {with perpetual check.}) 32... Bg7 33. Rhg3 Rc7 {Everyone iscovered and Black now can slowly try and create a passed pawn on the queenside.} 34. Re3 {Threatening a cheapo on e8.} Rf7 35. Rh3 {White has no way to makeprogress and can only wait.} b6 $1 {The greater Black's grip on the lightsquares, the more acute White's pain. Black threatens a sneaky little matingattack, starting with ...Qa8+!.} 36. Qd5 {Amin covers the long diagonal.} Qe837. Rh4 {One of those just-in-case moves. Black wasn't yet threatening ...Be4+.} Re7 38. Qg2 Bf6 $1 39. Rf4 {The embarrassed rook's mucusy cough is nothingshort of a bronchial white flag of surrender. This allows ...Be4.} ({However,White is unable to save himself in the line} 39. Rh3 Rg7 $1 40. Qf3 Rxg1+ 41.Kxg1 Qg6+ 42. Kf2 Qc2+ 43. Qe2 Bd4+ 44. Kf3 Qc6+ 45. Kg4 Bf6 46. Kg3 Kg7 {. Black slowly un